Project Title: Vivid Hadana E-Commerce Consultancy Project
Course: IDB 10103 â€“ Introduction to Computing & Information Systems

Role: Lead Systems Consultant

Timeline: July 2018 Semester

Project Overview
Commissioned as a technical consultant to design, develop, and launch a fully functional B2C (Business-to-Consumer) e-commerce platform. The project required the implementation of a complete information system using the System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) framework to solve real-world digital retail challenges.

Technical Implementation (SDLC Framework)
To meet the academic requirements of CLO3 and CLO4, the project was executed through the five stages of the SDLC:

1. Planning & Analysis: Conducted a feasibility study to identify user requirements for a modern e-commerce environment, focusing on user accessibility and informative content delivery.

2. System Design: Architected the site map including an Informative Homepage, Product/Service Details, and a secure "About Us" section to build brand trust.

3. Implementation: Developed the front-end interface and integrated a simple database system to manage product listings and user interactions.

4. Security & Authentication: Implemented a secure Login Page and membership portal to ensure data privacy for registered users.

5. Support & Maintenance: Established a maintenance plan for site updates and security patches to ensure long-term system stability.

Key Features Developed
Database Management: Integrated database concepts to handle dynamic product/service catalogs.

Secure Authentication: User login system for personalized customer experiences.

Responsive UI/UX: Designed using Wix to ensure a seamless experience across mobile and desktop devices.

Informative Architecture: Comprehensive pages detailing business values and service offerings.

Learning Outcomes Achieved
CLO 3: Successfully implemented an Information System in a commercial environment using standardized development methodologies (PLO6).

CLO 4: Applied the full SDLC and database concepts to solve complex business problems through a functional prototype.
